# =============================================================================
# UD_Basaa — sample treebank (bootstrap, v0.1)
# 5 sentences, hand-analyzed from glossed sources in ../docs and ../corpora.
# Tier conventions:
#   FORM   = practical (mostly toneless) orthography, word-level tokens
#   LEMMA  = root/stem
#   MISC   Gloss= Leipzig morpheme gloss ; Morph= morpheme segmentation ; Eng= token sense
#   # text_eng / # text_fra = free-translation tiers ("translated")
# Noun-class concord is encoded with NounClass=Bantu<n> features.
# Subject-agreement + TAM are kept ON the verb token (one word) with features;
#   the alternative (multiword-token split) is discussed in syntactic_analysis.md.
# =============================================================================

# sent_id = bas-hm2014-7a
# text = Sogol antehe boonge
# text_eng = The grandfather saw the children.
# text_fra = Le grand-père a vu les enfants.
# source = Hamlaoui & Makasso (2014), ex. (7a); docs/Hamlaoui_Makasso_2014_HighTone_PhonPhrases_Basaa.pdf
1	Sogol	sokol	NOUN	_	NounClass=Bantu1|Number=Sing	2	nsubj	_	Gloss=1.grandfather|Eng=grandfather
2	antehe	tehe	VERB	_	NounClass=Bantu1|Tense=Past	0	root	_	Gloss=1.AGR-PST-see|Morph=a-n-tehe|Eng=saw
3	boonge	oonge	NOUN	_	NounClass=Bantu2|Number=Plur	2	obj	_	Gloss=2-children|Eng=children

# sent_id = bas-hm2014-7b
